
[1]poke-weed

   PO'KE-WEED, n. The popular name of a plant of the genus Phytolacca,
   otherwise called cocum and garget; a native of N. America. As a
   medicine, it has emetic and cathartic qualities, and has had some
   reputation as a remedy for rheumatism. It was formerly called in
   Virginia, pocan.
